Organ trafficking in Russia has been a growing concern, with doctors accused of illegal kidney removal.
A new law aims to allow local hospitals to perform organ transplants, addressing the shortage.
In China, reports reveal unethical practices of harvesting organs from Falungong practitioners.
The Philippines also faces issues with organ trafficking, particularly among the poor.
In the US, efforts are being made to increase organ donations, including incentivizing inmates.
Meanwhile, controversies surround a transplant program closure at Kaiser Permanente.
Globally, regulations are being considered to streamline organ donation processes and prevent abuse.
